item.description:
Relevance Direct observation (extensible to experimental science) is a valuable source of knowledge in some cases (even mokSha according to some), but not in others (dharma). Primacy over text Literal understanding of sayings in the veda-s and shAstra-s, contradicting direct observation (and science), is considered naive and wrong.
Brilliant shrI rAmAnuja clearly limiting scope of shAstra, mincing no words (while tearing up shankara&rsquo;s contra-pratyaxa jagan-mithyA-vAda)-
आकाश-वाय्व्-आदि&ndash;भूत&ndash;
तद्-आरब्ध-शब्द-स्पर्शादि-युक्त-मनुष्यत्वादि&ndash;
संस्थान-संस्थित-पदार्थ-ग्राहि प्रत्यक्षम् ।
